Hongkong Bank to open new branch in Shanghai . Hongkong & Shanghai Banking Corp said on Monday it has received approval from the People ' s Bank of China to open a new branch in the Pudong district of Shanghai . The new branch will serve as the bank ' s main branch in the Chinese city , it said in a statement . The approval coincided with the central bank ' s naming of Hongkong Bank , the banking unit of HSBC Holdings Plc , to conduct Chinese currency business in Shanghai . Three other banks - - Citibank , Tokyo - Mitsubishi Bank and the Industrial Bank of Japan - - also received approval to conduct renminbi business . Only banks with branches in Pudong are allowed to apply to do local currency business . - - Hong Kong Newsroom ( 852 ) 2843 6441 
